1. What is variable?
A variable in Java is a container used to store data values during program execution.
int -> age = 25;
int ->data type
age ->variable name
25 ->value
2. Types of variable in java
They are three main type of variable
2.1 Local variable
A variable declared inside a method or block.
void test() {
    int a = 10;  // local variable
}
Key Points
✔ Scope → only inside method
✔ Must be initialized before use
✔ Stored in stack memory
2.2 Instance variable
A variable declared inside a class but outside any method, and belongs to object.
class Test {
    int a = 10;  // instance variable
}
Key Points
✔ Each object has its own copy
✔ Stored in heap memory
✔ Access using object
2.3 Static Variable(class variable)
A variable declared with static keyword, shared among all objects.
class Test {
    static int count = 0;
}
Key Points
✔ One copy for all objects
✔ Memory efficient
✔ Access using class name
QUICK COMPARISON (IMPORTANT)
Feature	      Local	         Instance	     Static
Location	Inside method	Inside class	Inside class
Scope	    Method only	    Object	        Class
Memory	    Stack	        Heap	        Method area
Access	    Direct	        Object	        Class name
INTERVIEW TRAPS
Where local variable stored?
✔ Stack
Default value of local variable?
No default value (must initialize)
Default value of instance/static?
Yes (0, null, false)
Which variable is shared?
Static variable
Real QA Example
class LoginPage {
    String username; // instance
    static int count = 0; // static
    void login() {
        int attempts = 1; // local
    }
